%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F609421eaf22c6b00185dcaab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22562%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%2C%20Jen%20Glantz.%3Cp%3EJen%20Glantz%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWith%20inflation%20raising%20the%20cost%20of%20everything%2C%20I've%20been%20looking%20for%20creative%20ways%20to%20save%20money.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EI'm%20selling%20items%20around%20the%20house%20that%20I%20no%20longer%20need%2C%20and%20reducing%20my%20electricity%20use.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBeing%20more%20mindful%20of%20food%20waste%20is%20helping%20me%20save%20money%20at%20the%20grocery%20store.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20inflation%20causing%20the%20price%20of%20food%20and%20household%20items%20to%20skyrocket%2C%20I've%20become%20obsessed%20with%20finding%20ways%20to%20save%20more%20money%20every%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20fully%20remote%20worker%2C%20I%20spend%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20at%20home.%20For%20the%20last%20two%20months%2C%20I've%20started%20to%20brainstorm%20ways%20that%20I%20can%20change%20my%20habits%20around%20the%20house%20in%20order%20to%20save%20%24200%2C%20or%20more%2C%20every%20single%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20making%20a%20few%20changes%20and%20trying%20out%20new%20behaviors%2C%20here%20are%20the%20four%20ways%20I%20was%20able%20to%20make%20that%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Selling%20items%20around%20the%20house%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20my%20favorite%20ways%20to%20make%20extra%20money%20on%20the%20weekends%20is%20by%20selling%20items%20I%20have%20around%20the%20house%20that%20I%20don't%20use%20or%20don't%20need%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spend%2045%20minutes%20every%20Sunday%20rounding%20up%20anything%20that%20I%20want%20to%20try%20to%20sell%20before%20listing%20those%20items%20on%20apps%20like%20Poshmark%20(great%20for%20clothing%20and%20shoes)%2C%20Facebook%20Marketplace%20(great%20for%20furniture%20or%20random%20items%20like%20rollerblades%2C%20dishes%2C%20or%20household%20accessories)%2C%20or%20OfferUp%20(great%20for%20furniture%20or%20household%20accessories).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20month%20I%20was%20able%20to%20make%20%2475%20by%20selling%20three%20furniture%20items%2C%20and%20this%20month%2C%20so%20far%2C%20I've%20made%20around%20%24100%20selling%20clothes%20and%20shoes.%20While%20I%20do%20spend%20some%20of%20that%20money%2C%20I%20try%20to%20save%2025%25%20to%2050%25%20and%20put%20the%20cash%20in%20either%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-an-emergency-fund%5C%22%3Eemergency%20fund%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20my%20general%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-high-yield-savings-accounts-rates-right-now%5C%22%3Esavings%20account%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Lowering%20my%20electric%20bill%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20look%20at%20my%20electric%20bill%20during%20the%20summer%20months%2C%20I%20begin%20to%20sweat.%20In%20an%20average%20month%2C%20the%20electric%20bill%20for%20my%20500-square-foot%20one-bedroom%20apartment%20can%20hover%20around%20%24180.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20effort%20to%20lower%20the%20bill%20as%20much%20as%20possible%2C%20I've%20started%20to%20get%20strategic%20about%20my%20habits%20around%20the%20house%20using%20advice%20from%20my%20local%20energy%20provider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20am%20guilty%20of%20leaving%20the%20house%20with%20the%20lights%20and%20the%20air%20on%2C%20even%20when%20I%20don't%20plan%20to%20be%20home%20for%20hours.%20I%20put%20a%20sticky%20note%20on%20my%20front%20door%20reminding%20me%20to%20shut%20everything%20off%20before%20I%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20blasting%20my%20air%20conditioning%20all%20day%2C%20since%20I%20work%20from%20home%2C%20I've%20started%20to%20lower%20our%20shades%20to%20keep%20the%20apartment%20cooler%20and%20run%20the%20air%20for%2020%20minutes%20at%20a%20time%20before%20turning%20it%20off%20for%2040%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20using%20appliances%20(like%20the%20dishwasher%20or%20in-unit%20washer%20and%20dryer)%2C%20rather%20than%20turning%20them%20on%20three%20to%20four%20times%20a%20week%2C%20I've%20limited%20my%20dishwashing%20to%20once%20a%20week%20(handwashing%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20items)%20and%20doing%20laundry%20once%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20amount%20of%20the%20electric%20bill%20can%20change%20based%20on%20many%20factors%2C%20I'm%20hoping%20that%20by%20getting%20more%20rigid%20about%20these%20behavior%20shifts%2C%20I%20can%20knock%20off%20at%20least%20%2420%20a%20month%20from%20that%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Being%20mindful%20about%20food%20waste%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20months%20ago%2C%20I%20took%20an%20audit%20of%20how%20much%20I%20spend%20every%2030%20days%20on%20groceries%20and%20realized%20my%20total%20was%20around%20%24600.%20I%20started%20to%20notice%20that%20I%20could%20shave%20some%20money%20off%20that%20amount%20if%20I%20was%20smarter%20about%20not%20only%20how%20I%20was%20buying%20these%20food%20items%2C%20but%20also%20about%20how%20I%20was%20making%20sure%20they%20didn't%20go%20to%20waste.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20getting%20better%20at%20searching%20for%20coupons%20before%20heading%20to%20the%20store%2C%20and%20buying%20more%20frozen%20produce%2C%20I%20found%20another%20simple%20way%20that%20I%20could%20save%20%2415%20to%20%2420%20a%20week%20on%20groceries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20letting%20food%20items%20go%20to%20waste%2C%20I%20found%20ways%20to%20turn%20them%20into%20meals%20and%20put%20them%20in%20the%20freezer%20before%20they%20went%20bad.%20For%20example%2C%20last%20week%2C%20I%20had%20an%20unused%20garlic%20bulb%2C%20onion%2C%20potato%2C%20and%20zucchini%20that%20were%20all%20about%20to%20go%20bad%20before%20I%20could%20consume%20them.%20I%20turned%20them%20into%20soup%20and%20put%20the%20container%20in%20the%20freezer.%20I%20can%20have%20that%20soup%20for%20lunch%20for%20at%20least%20two%20or%20three%20days%2C%20saving%20me%20money%20on%20having%20to%20buy%20other%20items%20to%20eat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20realized%20that%20every%20week%20I%20was%20buying%20a%20new%20loaf%20of%20bread%20(around%20%245)%20and%20was%20only%20eating%20a%20third%20of%20the%20loaf.%20I%20started%20to%20put%20the%20leftover%20bread%20in%20the%20freezer%20and%20now%20only%20buy%20bread%20every%20three%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20these%20techniques%20has%20helped%20me%20save%20around%20%2460%20to%20%2480%20a%20month%20on%20my%20grocery%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Buying%20off-brand%20cleaning%20products%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20easy%20way%20I%20was%20able%20to%20save%20money%20on%20my%20grocery%20bill%20was%20by%20being%20mindful%20about%20buying%20generic%20or%20store-brand%20items%20over%20more%20popular%20and%20well-known%20brand%20items%20instead.%20When%20I%20started%20doing%20this%20with%20cleaning%20supplies%2C%20I%20noticed%20that%20I%20was%20saving%20anywhere%20from%20%2415%20to%20%2430%20a%20month%2C%20depending%20on%20what%20I%20needed%20to%20buy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20if%20I%20needed%20new%20dish%20soap%2C%20I%20found%20I%20was%20able%20to%20buy%20the%20store-brand%20version%20for%20%241%20instead%20of%20the%20%245%20dish%20soap%20I%20was%20buying%20from%20a%20major%20brand%20I%20was%20loyal%20to.%20When%20I%20switched%20most%20of%20my%20cleaning%20products%20away%20from%20well-known%20brands%2C%20my%20savings%20started%20to%20increase.%20Plus%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20store%20you%20shop%20at%2C%20you%20might%20even%20find%20more%20coupons%20offered%2C%20or%20buy-one%20get-one%20deals%2C%20if%20you%20buy%20the%20store%20brand%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBuild%20a%20Budget%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-budgeting-apps%5C%22%3Ebest%20budgeting%20apps%3C%2Fa%3E%20ca