S24%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20proposed%20bill%20would%20add%20an%20extra%20%244%20to%20%2410%20a%20month%20to%20streaming%20music%20fees.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMaking%20streaming%20music%20work%20better%20for%20artists%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20non-famous%20ones%20%E2%80%94%20is%20a%20real%20problem.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20this%20bill%20won't%20solve%20it%20because%20it's%20never%20going%20anywhere.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ELots%20of%20consumers%20like%20streaming%20music.%20Lots%20of%20musicians%20complain%20about%20streaming%20%E2%80%94%20they%20say%20it%20doesn't%20generate%20nearly%20as%20much%20revenue%20for%20them%20as%20they%20deserve%20and%20need.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20here's%20a%20proposal%20to%20help%20fix%20that%3A%20a%20tax%20that%20would%20increase%20American%20consumers'%20music%20streaming%20bills%20by%2050%25%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20you'd%20pay%20an%20extra%20%244%20to%20%2410%20a%20month%20for%20services%20like%20Spotify%20or%20Apple%20Music.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%5BRecord%20scratch.%5D%20What%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20proposal%20comes%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fd12t4t5x3vyizu.cloudfront.net%2Ftlaib.house.gov%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FLiving-Wage-for-Musicians-Act_Final-Text.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELiving%20Wage%20for%20Musicians%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20sponsored%20by%20Rep.%20Rashida%20Tlaib%20(D-Michigan)%20and%20Rep.%20Jamaal%20Bowman%20(D-New%20York).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20this%20one%20is%20obviously%20not%20going%20anywhere.%20I%20don't%20believe%20there%20was%20ever%20a%20time%20that%20Americans%20supported%20a%2050%25%20tax%20hike%20on%20anything%2C%20for%20any%20reason.%20But%20it's%20clearly%20not%20going%20to%20happen%20when%20lots%20of%20them%20are%20still%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20afford%20houses%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconsumer-confidence-economy-stock-market-gas-prices-eggs-vibes-recession-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeggs%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20a%20big%20inflation%20spike.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20also%20tell%20Tlaib%20and%20the%20bill's%20supporters%20don't%20really%20think%20this%20tax%20is%20going%20anywhere%2C%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20presumably%20why%20Tlaib's%20office%20doesn't%20spell%20out%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20tax%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftlaib.house.gov%2Fposts%2Ftlaib-introduces-living-wage-for-musicians-act%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannouncement%3C%2Fa%3E%20promoting%20the%20bill%20%E2%80%94%20it%20refers%20to%20it%20only%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bsmall%20fee.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20goes%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweareumaw.org%2Fmake-streaming-pay%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUnited%20Musicians%20and%20Allied%20Workers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20group%20that%20helped%20create%20the%20bill.%20And%20the%20same%20goes%20for%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fcommentisfree%2F2024%2Fmar%2F28%2Fnew-law-how-musicians-make-money-streaming%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eop-ed%20from%20Damon%20Krukowski%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20musician%20and%20UMAW%20member.%20None%20of%20them%20spell%20out%20what%20would%20happen%20to%20consumers'%20monthly%20bills%20if%20this%20went%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhich%2C%20frankly%2C%20made%20me%20think%20that%20Krukowski%20and%20his%20colleagues%20are%20trying%20to%20accomplish%20something%20else%20with%20this%20proposal.%20Though%20I'm%20not%20sure%20what%20that%20would%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20we%20got%20on%20the%20phone%20to%20discuss%20the%20bill%20this%20month%2C%20he%20said%20it's%20supposed%20to%20be%20taken%20literally%20and%20seriously.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20meant%20to%20be%20a%20workable%20solution%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeaving%20aside%20the%20non-starter%20of%20a%20tax%2C%20Krukowski%20has%20plenty%20of%20good%20points%20to%20make%20about%20how%20difficult%20it%20is%20for%20most%20musicians%20to%20make%20any%20kind%20of%20money%20from%20streaming.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmusic-royalties-artist-revenue-compared-spotify-apple-music-pandora-2019-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMany%20of%20which%20you've%20heard%20before%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20good%20bit%20of%20nuance%20Krukowski%20adds%20that%20you%20likely%20haven't%20heard%3A%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20the%20US%20government%20%3Cem%3Ealready%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20a%20role%20in%20distributing%20revenue%20to%20musicians%20(or%2C%20at%20least%2C%20people%20who%20own%20the%20rights%20to%20songs%20musicians%20write%20and%20perform).%20But%20that%20doesn't%20apply%20to%20much%20of%20the%20revenue%20on-demand%20music%20streamers%20collect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20lots%20of%20musicians%20take%20issue%20with%20deals%20big%20music%20labels%20strike%20with%20the%20likes%20of%20Spotify%20and%20how%20little%20of%20that%20comes%20back%20to%20artists%2C%20Krukowski%20says%20the%20bill%20is%20explicitly%20%3Cem%3Enot%3C%2Fem%3E%20trying%20to%20meddle%20with%20those%20deals.%20This%20is%20just%20supposed%20to%20add%20an%20additional%20revenue%20source%2C%20which%20would%20be%20distributed%20directly%20to%20artists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20back%20to%20that%20fee%2C%20which%20the%20bill%20spells%20out%20as%20%26quot%3Ban%20additional%20fee%20in%20an%20amount%20equal%20to%2050%20percent%20of%20the%20subscription%20fee%20charged%20by%20the%20service%20provider%2C%20except%20that%20such%20additional%20fee%20shall%20not%20be%20an%20amount%20less%20than%20%244%20or%20more%20than%20%2410.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.spotify.com%2Fus%2Fpremium%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpotify%20premium%20subscriber%2C%20paying%20a%20list%20price%20of%20%2411%20a%20month%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that%20would%20be%20an%20additional%20%245.50%20a%20month.%20(That%20theoretical%20money%20would