ngress%20chief%20went%20on%20to%20ask%20four%20pointed%20questions%20and%20accused%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20of%20being%20%26quot%3Bpersonally%20responsible%26quot%3B%20for%20%26quot%3Busurping%26quot%3B%20the%20powers%20of%20institutions%20and%20%26quot%3Bweakening%20our%20country%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20drew%20the%20Congress%20chief's%20rejoinder%20was%20a%20blistering%20post%20by%20PM%20Modi%20earlier%20today%20after%20600%20lawyers%20wrote%20to%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%2C%20alleging%20attempts%20by%20%26quot%3Ba%20vested%20interest%20group%26quot%3B%20to%20undermine%20the%20judiciary's%20integrity%20and%20defame%20courts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20browbeat%20and%20bully%20others%20is%20vintage%20Congress%20culture.%20Five%20decades%20ago%2C%20they%20itself%20had%20called%20for%20a%20'committed%20judiciary'%20-%20they%20shamelessly%20want%20commitment%20from%20others%20for%20their%20selfish%20interests%2C%20but%20desist%20from%20any%20commitment%20towards%20the%20nation%2C%26quot%3B%20PM%20Modi%20said%20in%20a%20post%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20Twitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELater%20in%20the%20evening%2C%20the%20Congress%20chief%2C%20in%20his%20statement%20posted%20on%20X%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BAs%20you%20consider%20India's%20institutions%20to%20be%20your%20personal%20property%2C%20I%20have%20some%20questions%20for%20you%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-media-max-width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EPM%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fnarendramodi%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40narendramodi%3C%2Fa%3E%20ji%2C%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnYou%20are%20talking%20about%20Judiciary.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn1.%20You%20conveniently%20forget%20that%204%20senior-most%20Supreme%20Court%20judges%20were%20forced%20to%20hold%20an%20unprecedented%20press%20conference%20and%20warn%20against%20%26quot%3Bdestruction%20of%20Democracy%26quot%3B.%20That%20happened%20under%20your%20regime.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnOne%20of%20the%20judges%20was%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20(%40kharge)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fkharge%2Fstatus%2F1773351581070578014%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EMarch%2028%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20question%20pertained%20to%20an%20unprecedented%20press%20conference%20in%20January%202018%20by%20four%20judges%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20who%20went%20public%20with%20their%20complaints%20against%20the%20then%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%2C%20Dipak%20Misra.%20An%20independent%20judiciary%20is%20essential%20for%20a%20functioning%20democracy%2C%20the%20judges%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhy%20was%20one%20of%20the%20judges%20nominated%20by%20your%20Govt%20to%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%3F%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Kharge%20asked%20next%2C%20refering%20to%20the%20unprecedented%20Upper%20House%20nomination%20of%20former%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20Ranjan%20Gogoi%20in%202020.%20The%20recommendation%20by%20then%20President%20of%20India%20Ram%20Nath%20Kovind%20is%20unprecedented%20%E2%80%93%20till%20then%2C%20no%20Chief%20Justice%20had%20been%20nominated%20to%20the%20Upper%20House%20by%20the%20head%20of%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhy%20has%20your%20party%20fielded%20a%20former%20high%20court%20judge%20from%20West%20Bengal%20for%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%3F%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Kharge%20has%20also%20asked%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20former%20Calcutta%20High%20Court%20judge%20Abhijeet%20Gangopadhyay%2C%20whose%20move%20into%20electoral%20politics%20has%20raised%20eyebrows.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Kharge%20also%20questioned%20why%20the%20government%20brought%20the%20National%20Judicial%20Appointments%20Commission%20(NJAC)%20that%20was%20struck%20down%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20The%20Congress%2C%20though%2C%20had%20supported%20the%20constitutional%20amendmen